rosecutor said. He said that the alleged offences contravened Sections 168 and 411 of the Criminal laws of Lagos State 2015. The Chief Magistrate, Mr A. A. Fashola, granted each of the defendants N50, 000 bail with two sureties in like sum. Fashola ordered that the sureties must be gainfully employed and show evidence of two years’ tax payment to the Lagos State Government. He added that such sureties must reside within the court’s jurisdiction, and adjourned the case until Feb.27, for mention. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that that conspiracy is punishable with two years’ imprisonment while breach of the peace attracts six months’ jail term or N50, 000 fine. (NAN) VANGUARD The police in Ikeja on Thursday arraigned two teenagers, who allegedly threatened to stab a neighbour cautioning them against hemp smoking. The defendants – Yusuf Olaiya and Rasak Alade, both aged 18 – were charged along with Isiaka Olarinde, 30, before an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court. The trio, however, pleaded… November 29, 2019 In "News" A 40-year-old estate agent, Victor Ojeifor, on Monday appeared at the Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court for alleged wandering in a Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG) premises with an intent to steal. The defendant, a resident of Alagbao in Lagos, was arraigned on a one-count charge of breach of peace… October 21, 2019 In "News" A 19-year-old painter, Oladipupo Ibukun , who allegedly stole N18, 000 and a cell phone valued at N19, 000, was on Wednesday arraigned in an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court. November 1, 2017 In "News"